HEADWORD: maccaroni wheat
<hw>maccaroni wheat</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A type of wheat
(<spn>Triticum durum</spn>) with hard dark-colored kernels high in
gluten and used for bread and pasta; grown especially in South Russia,
North Africa, and North central North America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> durum, durum wheat, hard wheat, <spn>Triticum
durum</spn>, <spn>Triticum turgidum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macco</ent>⟦br⟧
